"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Visibility","text":"Visibility","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore10VisibilityO"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","text":"View","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"},{"text":"\n","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use this modifier when you want to omit a label from one or more","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"labeled content in your user interface. For example, the first ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Toggle","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in the following example hides its label:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["VStack {","    Toggle(isOn: $toggle1) {","        Text(\"Toggle 1\")","    }","    .labelsVisibility(.hidden)","","    Toggle(isOn: $toggle2) {","        Text(\"Toggle 2\")","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/VStack","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" in the example above centers the first toggle’s control"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"element in the available space, while it centers the second toggle’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"combined label and control element:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Always provide a label for controls, even when you hide the label,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"because OpenSwiftUI uses labels for other purposes, including accessibility.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On iOS, a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Picker"},{"type":"text","text":" within a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Menu"},{"type":"text","text":" hides its label by default. You can use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this modifier to explicitly show the label in that context:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["Menu {","    Picker(\"Flavor\", selection: $selectedFlavor) {","        Text(\"Chocolate\").tag(Flavor.chocolate)","        Text(\"Vanilla\").tag(Flavor.vanilla)","        Text(\"Strawberry\").tag(Flavor.strawberry)","    }","    .labelsVisibility(.visible)","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This modifier doesn’t work for all labels. It applies to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/LabeledContent","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" elements, including controls like "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Picker"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Toggle","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", but not to controls like a bordered button where the label"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is inside the button’s border."}]}],"style":"note","type":"aside"}]}],"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Rectangle"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"Controls the visibility of labels of any controls contained within this","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"view.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Rectangle\/labelsVisibility(_:)"},"references":{"doc:/